There are several suspicious processes with open sockets:

1. Process ID 880 (svchost.exe) has a socket open on port 1185 with TCP protocol.
2. Process ID 1244 (svchost.exe) has sockets open on ports 1189 and 2869 with TCP protocol.
3. Process ID 4 (System) has a socket open on port 139 with TCP protocol.
4. Process ID 2024 (alg.exe) has a socket open on port 1026 with TCP protocol.

These processes and their associated sockets should be further investigated as they could potentially be related to the suspicious activity observed. It is advisable to analyze the network traffic and communication patterns of these processes to determine if any malicious activities are ongoing.
